# GitHub FGP Integration

Use `fgp call github.*` commands for fast GitHub operations via persistent daemon.

## Available Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `github.repos` | List your repositories |
| `github.issues` | List issues for a repository |
| `github.notifications` | Get unread notifications |
| `github.pr_status` | Check PR status for current branch |
| `github.user` | Get authenticated user info |

## Commands

### List Repositories
```bash
fgp call github.repos -p '{"limit": 10}'
```

### List Issues
```bash
fgp call github.issues -p '{"repo": "owner/repo", "state": "open", "limit": 10}'
```
Parameters: `repo` (required), `state` (optional: open/closed/all), `limit` (optional)

### Get Notifications
```bash
fgp call github.notifications
```

### Check PR Status
```bash
fgp call github.pr_status -p '{"repo": "owner/repo"}'
```

### Get User Info
```bash
fgp call github.user
```

## Setup

1. Ensure gh CLI is authenticated: `gh auth login`
2. Start daemon: `fgp start github`
3. Test: `fgp call github.user`

## Response Format

All commands return JSON with structured data.
